records.addlTxt:
Defendant Demetrius Jermaine Armstrong in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT to each other with credit for 2 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  AODA assessment/recommended treatment;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Obtain CCW permit;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Successfully complete 50 hours of community service (as to Count 1 only);
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment; cash bail on deposit to be applied.

Court ordered restitution set at $0.00.
